description:
Is there anything you can really trust? Where can you find real, authentic answers to life‚Äôs greatest questions? ‚ÄúThe Great Controversy‚Äù outlines a great cosmic battle between good and evil, and it is centered around you. How can you survive? What is the answer?

In this episode, we will explore the history of the great battle between good and evil. It will show the fall of Lucifer and demonstrate that God has a plan that will overwhelm the devil‚Äôs attack.

This is the 14th episode in the AWR Master Class series called Unlocking Bible Prophecies. You can follow the series and interact LIVE at: 

https://bible.awr.org/the-blueprint/

ABOUT CAMI OETMAN
Ten years ago, Cami Oetman had a real encounter with God that would change her life forever. She was a successful entrepreneur at the time, and the transition wasn't easy. However, the truth Cami will share in this series was so compelling that she knew every human being in the world should experience the love of Jesus as she had.

Within three years, she had preached 350 Bible presentations. Today, as a vice president for Adventist World Radio, Cami travels the world documenting the miracles that take place when people give their hearts to Jesus.

It may seem difficult to imagine yourself understanding Bible prophecy. Cami couldn‚Äôt either. She had spent two decades in the modeling world‚Äîin front of and behind the camera. She had also used her master‚Äôs degree in social work to care for hospice patients. She then started a successful retail business. But no one can predict how they will react when they have a real experience with God!

THE BLUEPRINT
Have you ever been lost without directions or a map? Did you know that God gave us a roadmap to navigate our lives? In order to read God‚Äôs map, we must first understand the Great Controversy, a cosmic war between God and Satan. 
 
The Great Controversy began with Lucifer, a heavenly angel, proclaiming in Isaiah 14:14 that he wanted to be ‚Äúlike the Most High.‚Äù The problem was that Lucifer wanted to be Holy without following the law of God, which reflects His character of love. 

God needed a jury to judge Lucifer (who became Satan) fairly and justly (Deuteronomy 19:15), so He created humans, partially to serve as jurors and demonstrate His true character (1 Corinthians 6:2-3). 

Adam and Eve chose to sin against God, disqualifying them from jury selection, because they were no longer law-abiding citizens. The Gospel was given to restore humanity to be sound jurors who can distinguish from right and wrong. God knew that we would need a map in order to make our way back to heaven. What is this blueprint?

The Sanctuary is a unique structure that represents God‚Äôs house among His people (Exodus 25:8). It is also the blueprint to God‚Äôs plan of salvation, with each piece of furniture symbolizing a part of the Gospel message. God shows His plan to deliver His people through this blueprint. 

God also gives prophecies, which are like landmarks through time. Our first landmark is in the book of Daniel: the 70-Week Prophecy that foretells the First Coming of the Messiah (Daniel 9:24-27). Israel is not prepared for Jesus‚Äô coming and rejects Him. When Jesus died on the cross, the veil of the sanctuary was torn in two, signifying the end of the earthly blueprint (Matthew 27:51). 
 
The second landmark, the 1,260-Year Prophecy, states that the little horn would rise in power (Daniel 7:19, 25).  

The third landmark, the 2,300-Year Prophecy, tells us that the Sanctuary will be cleansed (Daniel 8:14). We believe that this period of time ended in 1844. Over a period of 500 years, God used the Reformation to restore His truth to the world using everyday Christians like you and me. 
 
Finally, we come to our last landmark, the Third Angel‚Äôs Message. Revelation 15 and 16 tell us that the seven last plagues are inflicted on those who ignore and reject God‚Äôs message. However, those who choose to receive God‚Äôs seal are safe (Psalms 91:1, 2). The seal of the living God marks the end of our journey (Revelation 7:1-4). 
 
In Revelation 12:10, Satan accuses humanity of falling away from God. However, when God opens the books, heaven‚Äôs records show that all our sins have been blotted out. Yes, our merciful God is willing to wipe all our sins away! No matter what you have done, Jesus has enough mercy to cover you.
